# Docker Rules

## Required Files
- Every project must have `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` from day one
- `.env` for config, `.env.example` as template (no real keys)

## docker-compose.yml
- All services (db, bot, webapp, auxiliary) defined in one compose file
- Health checks for dependent services (`depends_on` + `condition: service_healthy`)
- Named volumes for persistent data (e.g. `postgres_data`)
- Use `restart: unless-stopped` for production services

## Dockerfile
- Use multi-stage builds for production
- Pin base image versions
- Copy only necessary files (use `.dockerignore`)

## Development
- Mount source code via volumes for hot-reload in dev mode
- Use `docker-compose up --build -d` for local dev
- Logs: `docker-compose logs -f <service>`

## Environment
- All secrets via `.env`, never hardcoded
- Pass env vars through `environment:` block in compose
